In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims May 15, 2020, as Peace Officers Memorial Day and designates May 10 through May 16, 2020, as Police Week. He commends the law enforcement community for their bravery and dedication to protecting and serving the American people. The President emphasizes the importance of supporting law enforcement officers by providing them with the necessary resources and working towards a time when they receive the respect they deserve. He also mentions initiatives such as the Presidential Commission on Law Enforcement and the Administration of Justice and the National Blue Alert Network, which aim to improve the relationship between law enforcement and the communities they serve. The President calls on all Americans to observe Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week by participating in appropriate ceremonies and activities, and encourages the display of the flag from homes and businesses.